(1, 'Yangon', 'Myanmar', 'Trip to Yangon, Myanmar: Exploring the Enchanting Golden City.', 'Embark on a mesmerizing 10-day journey to Yangon, Myanmar\'s captivating cultural hub, where ancient traditions intertwine with modernity. With its rich history, vibrant markets, and breathtaking landmarks, this trip promises an unforgettable experience for every traveler. Priced at $2,984 per person, you\'ll immerse yourself in the city\'s charm and discover its hidden gems.\n\nDay 1 - Arrival and Introduction to Yangon\nUpon arrival at Yangon International Airport, you\'ll be greeted by our friendly guide and transferred to your luxurious accommodation. Settle into your well-appointed room and enjoy your first taste of Myanmar\'s warm hospitality.\n\nDay 2 - Exploring the Old and the New\nStart your day with a visit to the iconic Shwedagon Pagoda, a magnificent golden stupa that towers over the city. Stroll through Bogyoke Aung San Market, where you can shop for exquisite Burmese handicrafts, jewelry, and textiles. In the evening, take a leisurely walk along Yangon River to witness a stunning sunset.\n\nDay 3 - Cultural Immersion in Yangon\nToday, dive into Yangon\'s cultural heritage with visits to the National Museum and the Reclining Buddha at Chauk Htat Gyi Pagoda. Experience traditional Burmese dance performances and sample local delicacies during a vibrant cultural show.\n\nDay 4 - Day Trip to Bago\nEmbark on a day trip to Bago, a historic city known for its ancient temples and pagodas. Explore the magnificent Shwemawdaw Pagoda, visit the reclining Shwethalyaung Buddha, and learn about the local Mon culture.\n\nDay 5 - Yangon\'s Art and Architecture\nDiscover Yangon\'s burgeoning art scene by visiting contemporary art galleries and studios. Marvel at the city\'s architectural wonders, including the colonial-era buildings in downtown Yangon.\n\nDay 6 - Culinary Delights\nIndulge in a culinary adventure with a guided food tour. Sample authentic Burmese cuisine at bustling local eateries and learn about the flavors that define Myanmar\'s gastronomy.\n\nDay 7 - Yangon\'s Hidden Gems\nExplore off-the-beaten-path attractions, such as the Secretariat Building and Kandawgyi Park. Enjoy a serene boat ride on Kandawgyi Lake, surrounded by lush gardens and stunning views of the Shwedagon Pagoda.\n\nDay 8 - Leisure Day\nSpend a relaxing day at your luxurious accommodation, enjoying its amenities, spa treatments, and scenic views. Take this opportunity to recharge before more adventures.\n\nDay 9 - Yangon\'s Artisan Workshops\nVisit local workshops where skilled artisans create traditional handicrafts, from intricate wood carvings to lacquerware. Experience hands-on workshops and create your own unique piece of art.\n\nDay 10 - Farewell and Departure\nAfter a delicious breakfast, bid farewell to Yangon and its enchanting beauty. You\'ll be transferred to the airport for your onward journey, carrying cherished memories of your unforgettable 10-day adventure.\n\nAccommodation: Your accommodations will be a blend of luxury and comfort, offering elegant rooms, modern amenities, and stunning city views. Each property has been carefully selected to ensure a relaxing and rejuvenating stay.\n\nHighlights:\n\n    Shwedagon Pagoda: A must-visit, this glistening golden pagoda is a symbol of Myanmar\'s spirituality.\n    Bogyoke Aung San Market: Experience the vibrant market culture and shop for unique souvenirs.\n    Chauk Htat Gyi Pagoda: Admire the stunning Reclining Buddha statue, an awe-inspiring sight.\n    Art Galleries and Workshops: Immerse yourself in Yangon\'s thriving arts and crafts scene.\n    Culinary Adventure: Savor authentic Burmese flavors during a guided food tour.\n    Kandawgyi Park: Enjoy a tranquil escape in the heart of the city, surrounded by nature.\nExperience the allure of Yangon, Myanmar\'s golden city, where every corner reveals a story waiting to be told. Book your journey today and embark on an adventure that will leave you enchanted and inspired.', 10, '2023-10-18', 1985, 'YangonMI.jpg', 5, 0.0),
(2, 'Havana', 'Cuba', '15-Day Adventure: Havana & Beyond in Cuba.', 'Discover the vibrant rhythms, captivating history, and breathtaking landscapes of Cuba during this 15-day journey. Priced at $3,560 per person, this trip will take you from the enchanting streets of Havana to the stunning countryside, providing a comprehensive and immersive Cuban experience.\r\n\r\nDays 1-3: Arrival and Exploration of Havana\r\nArrive in Havana, a city alive with colors, music, and classic cars. Wander through the atmospheric streets of Old Havana, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, and marvel at its colonial architecture. Dive into the city\'s cultural scene, visiting art galleries, live music venues, and the famous Malecón waterfront.\r\n\r\nDays 4-6: Viñales Valley and Rural Charm\r\nHead to the picturesque Viñales Valley, known for its stunning limestone formations, tobacco fields, and traditional villages. Explore the valley on horseback or foot, meet local farmers, and learn about the art of cigar rolling. Embrace the slower pace of rural life and enjoy breathtaking sunsets over the tobacco fields.\r\n\r\nDays 7-9: Trinidad - Colonial Gem of the South\r\nTravel to Trinidad, a charming colonial town frozen in time. Cobblestone streets, colorful houses, and live salsa music create an enchanting atmosphere. Discover the nearby Topes de Collantes National Park, where hiking trails lead to waterfalls, lush forests, and natural pools.\r\n\r\nDays 10-12: Beach Bliss in Varadero\r\nEscape to Varadero\'s pristine beaches and turquoise waters. Relax under swaying palms, indulge in water sports, or explore nearby coral reefs. Enjoy the lively nightlife and be swept away by the rhythms of salsa at beachside clubs.\r\n\r\nDays 13-15: Return to Havana and Farewell\r\nReturn to Havana for your final days in Cuba. Explore more neighborhoods, immerse yourself in Afro-Cuban culture, and visit the impressive Revolution Square. As your adventure comes to a close, relish the memories and experiences you\'ve gained during your unforgettable Cuban journey.\r\n\r\nAccommodation: Throughout the trip, enjoy a mix of accommodations, from charming colonial guesthouses in Havana and Trinidad to cozy casas in Viñales and beachfront resorts in Varadero.\r\n\r\nHighlights:\r\n\r\n    Havana\'s Old World Charms: Experience the allure of Havana\'s historic streets and vibrant culture.\r\nViñales Valley: Discover the stunning landscapes, tobacco farms, and rural life of Viñales.\r\nTrinidad\'s Timeless Beauty: Wander the cobblestone streets of Trinidad and explore its surroundings.\r\nVaradero\'s Beach Paradise: Relax on Varadero\'s pristine beaches and enjoy its lively atmosphere.\r\n    Cuban Culinary Delights: Savor traditional Cuban cuisine, from local paladares to street food stalls.\r\nMusic and Dance: Embrace the lively rhythms of Cuban music and learn to salsa dance.\r\n    Natural Wonders: Explore the lush landscapes of Viñales and the waterfalls of Topes de Collantes.\r\n\r\nThis 15-day journey through Cuba promises to reveal the country\'s rich history, vibrant culture, and breathtaking natural beauty. From the bustling streets of Havana to the serene countryside and picturesque beaches, every moment will be a celebration of Cuba\'s unique spirit. Book your trip now and immerse yourself in the heart and soul of this captivating country.', 15, '2024-01-02', 3560, 'HavanaMI.jpg', 3, 0.0),
(3, 'Rome, Florence, Venice', 'Italy', '14-Day Grand Tour of Italy: Rome, Florence, Venice.', 'Embark on a captivating 14-day journey through Italy\'s most iconic cities: Rome, Florence, and Venice. Priced at $3,780 per person, this itinerary will immerse you in Italy\'s rich history, art, culture, and culinary delights.\r\n\r\nDays 1-4: Rome - The Eternal City\r\nArrive in Rome, where ancient history and modern life blend seamlessly. Explore the Colosseum, Roman Forum, and the Vatican City\'s artistic treasures, including the Sistine Chapel. Wander through charming neighborhoods, savor authentic Italian cuisine at local trattorias, and throw a coin into the Trevi Fountain.\r\n\r\nDays 5-9: Florence - Renaissance Masterpiece\r\nTravel to Florence, the heart of the Renaissance. Marvel at Michelangelo\'s David at the Accademia Gallery, explore the Uffizi Gallery\'s art collection, and visit the iconic Duomo. Stroll across the Ponte Vecchio bridge and indulge in Tuscan flavors at local markets and eateries.\r\n\r\nDays 10-14: Venice - City of Canals and Romance\r\nArrive in Venice, a city of unparalleled charm and elegance. Glide along its iconic canals on a gondola, explore the historic St. Mark\'s Square, and visit the stunning St. Mark\'s Basilica. Delight in the unique craftsmanship of Murano glassblowers and savor Venetian cuisine in charming canal-side restaurants.\r\n\r\nAccommodation: Experience Italy\'s diverse accommodations, from luxurious hotels in Rome, boutique inns in Florence, to canal-view lodgings in Venice, all selected for their comfort and authenticity.\r\n\r\nHighlights:\r\n\r\nHistoric Rome: Explore ancient ruins, Vatican City, and the city\'s vibrant neighborhoods.\r\n    Artistic Florence: Immerse yourself in Renaissance art, architecture, and Tuscan flavors.\r\n    Enchanting Venice: Discover romantic canals, palaces, and the allure of Venetian life.\r\n    Culinary Experiences: Savor Italian delights from regional dishes to gelato and espresso.\r\n    Cultural Gems: Admire masterpieces by Michelangelo, Leonardo da Vinci, and Titian.\r\n    Local Markets: Shop for handmade crafts, leather goods, and artisanal products.\r\n    Gondola Ride: Glide through Venice\'s canals for an unforgettable romantic experience.\r\n\r\nPrice: $3,780 per person\r\n\r\nThis 14-day journey through Italy\'s most iconic cities promises an unforgettable blend of history, art, culture, and romance. From the grandeur of Rome to the elegance of Florence and the enchantment of Venice, every moment will be a celebration of Italy\'s rich heritage. Immerse yourself in the beauty and charm of Italy, where each city tells a unique story. Book your journey now and experience the best that Italy has to offer.', 14, '2023-11-15', 3780, 'VeniceMI.jpg,Rome.jpg,Florence.jpg', 13, 0.0),
(5, 'Beijing', 'China', '16-Day Beijing and Outskirts Exploration: A Journey Through History and Nature.\r\n', 'Embark on a captivating 16-day journey that combines the vibrant cultural tapestry of Beijing with the serene beauty of its outskirts. From imperial treasures to hidden gems, this itinerary offers a comprehensive experience that will immerse you in China\'s rich heritage and natural wonders.\r\n\r\nDay 1-4: Beijing Arrival and Exploration\r\nArrive in Beijing, a city where ancient traditions meet modern innovations. Visit the iconic Forbidden City, explore the historic Tiananmen Square, and wander through the winding alleyways of the Hutongs. Discover the stunning Temple of Heaven and savor Peking Duck, a local delicacy.\r\n\r\nDay 5-7: Great Wall Adventure\r\nEmbark on a journey to the majestic Great Wall of China. Hike along its winding paths and enjoy breathtaking panoramic views. Visit sections such as Mutianyu and Jinshanling, each with its unique charm and history.\r\n\r\nDay 8-10: Cultural Experiences\r\nDelve into Beijing\'s cultural treasures with visits to the Summer Palace, Lama Temple, and Confucius Temple. Witness traditional performances, such as Peking Opera and Chinese acrobatics. Explore the 798 Art District, showcasing modern creativity.\r\n\r\nDay 11-13: Chengde Retreat\r\nTravel to Chengde, a picturesque city known for its imperial summer resort and Buddhist temples. Explore the vast complex of Bishu Shanzhuang, a UNESCO World Heritage Site. Visit Putuo Zongcheng Temple, an architectural marvel reminiscent of Tibet.\r\n\r\nDay 14-16: Pingyao Ancient Town\r\nVenture to Pingyao, an exceptionally preserved ancient town with well-preserved Ming and Qing dynasty architecture. Wander through cobblestone streets, visit ancient city walls, and immerse yourself in the ambiance of a bygone era.\r\n\r\nTrip Highlights:\r\n\r\n    Walk on the iconic Great Wall of China and marvel at its engineering marvels and breathtaking vistas.\r\n    Immerse yourself in the grandeur of the Forbidden City and gain insights into China\'s imperial history.\r\n    Discover the tranquility of the Summer Palace and the spiritual atmosphere of Lama Temple.\r\n    Experience traditional Chinese arts, from Peking Opera to calligraphy, and witness the vibrant modern art scene.\r\n    Explore the serene beauty of Chengde\'s temples and escape to the peaceful Pingyao Ancient Town.\r\n\r\nAccommodations:\r\nThroughout your journey, you\'ll stay in a mix of comfortable hotels that blend modern amenities with cultural charm. From luxury accommodations in Beijing to boutique inns in Pingyao, you\'ll experience a range of lodging experiences that enhance your trip.\r\n\r\nEmbark on a remarkable journey through Beijing and its outskirts, where the past and present intertwine seamlessly, offering you a deeper understanding of China\'s rich history, culture, and natural beauty.', 16, '2022-12-24', 3500, 'BeijingMI.jpg', 1, 0.0),
(6, 'New Delhi, Jaipur, Agra', 'India', '8-Day Golden Triangle Tour: Exploring New Delhi, Jaipur, and Agra.', 'Embark on a mesmerizing 8-day journey through India\'s Golden Triangle, encompassing the bustling city of New Delhi, the vibrant Pink City of Jaipur, and the historical treasure trove of Agra. Experience the cultural diversity, architectural marvels, and rich history that define these iconic destinations.\r\n\r\nDay 1-2: Arrival in New Delhi\r\nArrive in the heart of India, New Delhi. Explore the contrast between Old Delhi\'s narrow lanes and bustling markets, and New Delhi\'s wide boulevards and grand government buildings. Visit the Jama Masjid, India Gate, Humayun\'s Tomb, and Qutub Minar. Immerse yourself in the vibrant markets of Chandni Chowk and Connaught Place.\r\n\r\nDay 3-4: Jaipur - The Pink City\r\nTravel to Jaipur, known as the Pink City due to its distinct rose-colored architecture. Visit the Amber Fort, where you can ascend on an elephant or Jeep for a regal experience. Explore the City Palace, Hawa Mahal (Palace of Winds), and Jantar Mantar astronomical observatory. Enjoy a rickshaw ride through the bustling markets.\r\n\r\nDay 5-6: Agra - The City of Love\r\nProceed to Agra, home to the iconic Taj Mahal. Marvel at this magnificent white marble masterpiece at sunrise, a symbol of eternal love. Explore the Agra Fort, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, and visit Itimad-ud-Daulah\'s Tomb, often referred to as the \"Baby Taj.\"\r\n\r\nDay 7-8: Fatehpur Sikri and Return to Delhi\r\nEn route to Delhi, visit Fatehpur Sikri, an abandoned Mughal city known for its stunning architecture. Explore its intricately designed buildings, courtyards, and mosques. Return to Delhi for some last-minute shopping or relaxation before departing.\r\n\r\nTrip Highlights:\r\n\r\n    Witness the iconic Taj Mahal at sunrise and feel the romantic allure of its architecture.\r\n    Explore the magnificent forts and palaces of Jaipur, including the opulent Amber Fort.\r\n    Immerse yourself in the bustling markets, art, and culture of each city, from Delhi\'s bazaars to Jaipur\'s textiles.\r\n    Experience the fusion of Mughal and Rajput architectural styles in Agra\'s historical monuments.\r\n    Discover the cultural heritage and traditions of Rajasthan through local cuisine, arts, and crafts.\r\n\r\nAccommodations:\r\nYour accommodations will range from comfortable city hotels to heritage properties that capture the essence of each destination. Enjoy modern amenities combined with traditional charm, enhancing your overall experience.\r\n\r\nEmbark on an unforgettable journey through India\'s Golden Triangle, where the captivating blend of history, architecture, and culture will leave you with memories that last a lifetime.', 814234, '2025-09-05', 1800, 'TajMahalMI.jpgMI.jpg,NewDelhi.jpg,Jaipur.jpg', 2, 0.0),
(7, 'Phi Phi Islands, Bangkok', 'Thailand', '9-Day Adventure: Discovering Bangkok and the Enchanting Phi Phi Islands.\n', 'Embark on a 9-day journey that seamlessly blends the vibrant energy of Bangkok with the pristine beauty of the Phi Phi Islands. Explore the bustling city streets, delve into cultural treasures, and bask in the breathtaking tropical paradise of Thailand\'s most renowned island destination.\n\nDay 1-3: Arrival in Bangkok\nTouch down in the dynamic city of Bangkok, where ancient traditions harmonize with modern skyscrapers. Visit the Grand Palace, home to the revered Emerald Buddha, and marvel at the intricate architecture. Cruise along the Chao Phraya River, exploring ornate temples and bustling markets. Explore the bustling night markets and indulge in Thai street food.\n\nDay 4-6: Phi Phi Islands - Tropical Paradise\nFly to Phuket and take a ferry to the idyllic Phi Phi Islands. These turquoise waters, powdery white beaches, and towering limestone cliffs create an awe-inspiring backdrop. Snorkel or dive in the crystal-clear waters, discovering vibrant marine life and coral reefs. Relax on Maya Bay\'s stunning beach and enjoy vibrant nightlife on Phi Phi Don.\n\nDay 7-9: Back to Bangkok and Cultural Immersion\nReturn to Bangkok and delve deeper into its cultural treasures. Discover the intricacies of Thai cuisine through a cooking class, learn about Buddhism at Wat Arun, and explore the bustling markets of Chatuchak. Experience a traditional Thai massage and enjoy a relaxing cruise on a traditional long-tail boat along the klongs (canals).\n\nTrip Highlights:\n\n    Bangkok\'s Contrasts: Witness the blend of ancient temples, vibrant street markets, and modern skyscrapers in Thailand\'s capital city.\n    Phi Phi Islands Magic: Immerse yourself in the natural beauty of the Phi Phi Islands, with opportunities for snorkeling, diving, and beach relaxation.\n    Grand Palace Marvel: Be awed by the opulent architecture and rich history of the Grand Palace and its Emerald Buddha.\n    Thai Cuisine Delight: Savor the flavors of Thailand through street food, bustling markets, and a cooking class.\n    Cultural Discoveries: Gain insights into Thai traditions, history, and spirituality through temple visits and local experiences.\n\nAccommodations:\nYour accommodations range from comfortable city hotels in Bangkok to beachfront resorts on the Phi Phi Islands. Experience a blend of modern comforts and tropical charm, offering you the perfect base for your adventures.\n\nPrice:\nThe estimated cost for this 9-day trip to Bangkok and the Phi Phi Islands, including accommodations, guided tours, transportation, meals, and activities, ranges from $1,500 to $2,200 per person. Prices can vary based on accommodation preferences, the time of year, and additional activities.\n\nEmbark on this 9-day journey that takes you from the bustling streets of Bangkok to the serene shores of the Phi Phi Islands. Experience the best of both worlds, where cultural immersion meets island paradise, leaving you with unforgettable memories of Thailand\'s beauty and charm.', 9, '2023-10-23', 2200, 'Bangkok.jpg,PhiPhiIslandsMI.jpg', 2, 0.0),
(8, 'Santorini', 'Greece', '5-Day Escape to Santorini: Idyllic Beauty and Mediterranean Charm.', 'Experience the enchanting allure of Santorini, Greece, on a 5-day journey that transports you to a world of white-washed buildings, turquoise waters, and mesmerizing sunsets. This Mediterranean gem offers a perfect blend of relaxation, culture, and natural beauty.\r\n\r\nDay 1: Arrival in Santorini\r\nArrive in Santorini and be welcomed by stunning views of the iconic caldera. Settle into your charming hotel overlooking the Aegean Sea and enjoy a leisurely stroll through the narrow streets of Fira, the capital. Savor your first taste of traditional Greek cuisine at a local taverna.\r\n\r\nDay 2: Exploring the Island\r\nDiscover Santorini\'s unique landscape with a visit to the dramatic Red Beach, known for its vibrant hues. Explore the ancient ruins of Akrotiri, often referred to as the \"Pompeii of the Aegean,\" and learn about the island\'s rich history. Unwind on Perissa Beach or enjoy a relaxing afternoon at your hotel\'s infinity pool.\r\n\r\nDay 3: Oia\'s Charm and Sunset Splendor\r\nVenture to the picturesque village of Oia, famous for its blue-domed churches and narrow alleys. Explore local boutiques, art galleries, and charming cafes. In the evening, prepare to be mesmerized by one of the world\'s most famous sunsets as the sky transforms into shades of pink, orange, and gold.\r\n\r\nDay 4: Wine Tasting and Island Relaxation\r\nEmbark on a wine-tasting journey through Santorini\'s vineyards, where volcanic soil produces unique flavors. Sip on distinctive Assyrtiko wine and immerse yourself in the island\'s viticulture. Spend the afternoon on a catamaran cruise, swimming in crystal-clear waters and taking in panoramic views of the caldera.\r\n\r\nDay 5: Farewell to Santorini\r\nIndulge in a leisurely breakfast with sea views before bidding farewell to Santorini. Reflect on your unforgettable experiences as you depart with a heart full of memories and a longing to return to this enchanting paradise.\r\n\r\nTrip Highlights:\r\n\r\n    Caldera Magic: Marvel at the breathtaking views of the caldera and sparkling Aegean Sea from your hotel and various viewpoints across the island.\r\n    Charming Villages: Wander through the charming villages of Fira and Oia, characterized by white-washed buildings, blue-domed churches, and charming alleys.\r\n    Spectacular Sunsets: Witness the awe-inspiring beauty of Santorini\'s sunsets, with Oia offering the perfect vantage point.\r\n    Ancient Treasures: Explore the ancient ruins of Akrotiri and gain insight into the island\'s history and archaeology.\r\n    Wine and Cuisine: Indulge in wine tasting and savor traditional Greek cuisine at local tavernas and restaurants.\r\n    Seaside Relaxation: Spend quality time on the island\'s unique beaches, whether relaxing or engaging in water activities.\r\n\r\nAccommodations:\r\nYour stay in Santorini includes carefully selected accommodations that capture the essence of the island\'s charm. Enjoy comfortable and stylish lodging with breathtaking views of the sea and the caldera.\r\n\r\nEmbark on this 5-day journey to Santorini and immerse yourself in the island\'s unique beauty, captivating culture, and serene atmosphere. Whether you\'re savoring local flavors, exploring ancient sites, or basking in the Mediterranean sun, Santorini promises an unforgettable escape.', 5, '2023-01-06', 1200, 'SantoriniMI.jpg', 6, 0.0),
(9, 'Paris', 'France', '5 Days in Paris: A Romantic Journey Through the City of Light.', 'Embark on a captivating 5-day adventure to the enchanting city of Paris, where art, history, and romance converge in a mesmerizing blend. From iconic landmarks to hidden gems, experience the essence of this world-renowned destination.\r\n\r\nDay 1: Arrival and Seine River Cruise\r\nArrive in Paris and settle into your elegant hotel. Start your journey with a leisurely Seine River cruise, where you\'ll be introduced to the city\'s most famous landmarks, including the Eiffel Tower, Notre-Dame Cathedral, and the Louvre Museum. Enjoy a delightful dinner at a classic Parisian bistro.\r\n\r\nDay 2: Exploring Parisian Icons\r\nVisit the Louvre Museum in the morning to witness the world\'s art treasures, including the enigmatic Mona Lisa. Afterward, take a stroll through the Tuileries Garden and continue to the Champs-Élysées, where you can indulge in shopping and dining. In the evening, ascend the Eiffel Tower for breathtaking panoramic views of the city.\r\n\r\nDay 3: Montmartre and Artistic Vibes\r\nExplore the charming Montmartre district, known for its artistic heritage. Visit the Sacré-Cœur Basilica and take in sweeping views of Paris. Discover quaint cafes, street art, and boutique shops in this bohemian neighborhood. In the evening, experience a cabaret show at the iconic Moulin Rouge.\r\n\r\nDay 4: Palace of Versailles\r\nTake a day trip to the opulent Palace of Versailles, a UNESCO World Heritage site. Explore the lavish palace, its stunning gardens, and the Hall of Mirrors. Learn about the history of the French monarchy and immerse yourself in the grandeur of the past.\r\n\r\nDay 5: Cultural Immersion and Farewell\r\nSpend your last day exploring Parisian neighborhoods like Le Marais or the Latin Quarter. Visit local markets, bistros, and boutiques. Enjoy a leisurely afternoon at the Luxembourg Gardens, where you can relax and soak up the Parisian atmosphere. As the sun sets, dine at a romantic riverside restaurant, reflecting on your unforgettable journey.\r\n\r\nTrip Highlights:\r\n\r\n    Eiffel Tower: Admire the iconic Eiffel Tower from various angles and ascend for spectacular city views.\r\n    Louvre Museum: Explore one of the world\'s most renowned art museums and marvel at its priceless collections.\r\n    Montmartre: Immerse yourself in the artistic ambiance of Montmartre, capturing the spirit of Parisian creativity.\r\n    Palace of Versailles: Step back in time at the opulent Palace of Versailles, a symbol of French royalty.\r\n    Moulin Rouge: Experience the glitz and glamour of a cabaret show at the historic Moulin Rouge.\r\n    Culinary Delights: Indulge in French cuisine at traditional bistros, savoring croissants, escargot, and more.\r\n    Local Gems: Discover charming neighborhoods, gardens, and hidden cafes that capture the city\'s essence.\r\n\r\nAccommodations:\r\nYour stay in Paris will be at carefully selected accommodations, ranging from elegant boutique hotels to luxurious lodgings, offering you comfort and convenience in the heart of the city.\r\n\r\nUncover the romance, art, and allure of Paris on this 5-day journey. From iconic landmarks to hidden corners, immerse yourself in the city\'s rich history and cultural treasures. Paris awaits, ready to enchant you with its timeless charm and captivating ambiance.', 5, '2023-09-14', 1500, 'ParisMI.jpg', 0, 0.0),
(10, 'Rio de Janeiro', 'Brazil', '7 Days in Rio de Janeiro: Samba, Sunsets, and Sights.', 'Experience the vibrant energy, stunning landscapes, and rich culture of Rio de Janeiro during an unforgettable 7-day journey. From the iconic landmarks to the lively neighborhoods, immerse yourself in the rhythms of samba, bask in the warmth of the sun, and explore the diverse facets of this captivating Brazilian city.\n\nDay 1: Arrival and Sunset at Sugarloaf Mountain\nArrive in Rio de Janeiro and check into your hotel with views of the coastline. Kick off your adventure with a cable car ride to Sugarloaf Mountain to witness the city\'s lights come to life during a breathtaking sunset.\n\nDay 2: Corcovado and Christ the Redeemer\nVisit the iconic Christ the Redeemer statue atop Corcovado Mountain. Enjoy panoramic views of Rio\'s coastline and lush hills. In the evening, explore the lively neighborhood of Lapa and its famous Selarón Steps.\n\nDay 3: Beach Day at Copacabana and Ipanema\nSpend your day relaxing on the golden sands of Copacabana and Ipanema beaches. Immerse yourself in the local beach culture, sip on coconut water, and enjoy refreshing dips in the ocean.\n\nDay 4: Tijuca Forest and Botanical Garden\nExplore the Tijuca Forest, the world\'s largest urban rainforest, through guided trails. Afterward, visit the Rio de Janeiro Botanical Garden to discover an array of tropical plants and towering palm trees.\n\nDay 5: Favela Tour and Local Cuisine\nEmbark on a guided tour of a favela, a unique experience that offers insight into Rio\'s complex social fabric. Enjoy a traditional Brazilian meal at a local eatery, savoring flavors that reflect the city\'s diverse culinary scene.\n\nDay 6: Lagoa Rodrigo de Freitas and Shopping\nSpend the morning paddle boating on Lagoa Rodrigo de Freitas, surrounded by lush greenery. In the afternoon, explore the upscale shopping districts of Ipanema and Leblon, where you can find Brazilian fashion and souvenirs.\n\nDay 7: Art and Farewell to Rio\nVisit the Rio Art Museum (MAR) to explore contemporary Brazilian art. Stroll through Santa Teresa, a bohemian neighborhood known for its art studios and charming streets. End your trip with a farewell dinner at a traditional churrascaria, indulging in Brazilian barbecue.\n\nHighlights:\n\n    Iconic Sights: Stand before Christ the Redeemer and Sugarloaf Mountain for breathtaking views.\n    Beach Bliss: Soak up the sun and surf at Copacabana and Ipanema beaches.\n    Local Culture: Explore a favela, witness the lively street art scene, and experience the city\'s rhythm.\n    Natural Beauty: Discover the lush landscapes of Tijuca Forest and Lagoa Rodrigo de Freitas.\n    Culinary Delights: Sample Brazilian cuisine and indulge in churrascaria dining.\n    Art and Bohemia: Immerse yourself in Rio\'s artistic and bohemian neighborhoods.\n\nAccommodations:\nStay in well-located hotels that offer comfort and proximity to the city\'s attractions, whether it\'s beachside luxury or boutique charm.\n\nDiscover the heartbeat of Rio de Janeiro as you dance to the rhythm of samba, bask under the Brazilian sun, and explore the city\'s vibrant neighborhoods. This 7-day journey promises an immersive experience that captures the essence of this iconic destination.', 7, '2023-11-10', 2500, 'RioDeJaneiroMI.jpg', 2, 0.0),
(11, 'Cairo, Alexandria', 'Egypt', '3 Days in Egypt: Exploring Cairo and Alexandria.', 'Embark on a whirlwind 3-day adventure to two of Egypt\'s most captivating cities: Cairo and Alexandria. Immerse yourself in the rich history, iconic landmarks, and vibrant culture of these two unique destinations.\r\n\r\nDay 1: Arrival in Cairo and Pyramids of Giza\r\nUpon arrival in Cairo, check into your hotel and begin your journey with a visit to the awe-inspiring Pyramids of Giza. Marvel at the Great Pyramid, Sphinx, and the ancient mysteries that surround them. Explore the nearby Solar Boat Museum to discover the intricacies of ancient shipbuilding.\r\n\r\nDay 2: Egyptian Museum and Islamic Cairo\r\nStart your day at the Egyptian Museum, home to an extensive collection of artifacts, including the treasures of Tutankhamun. Explore Islamic Cairo, wandering through the bustling Khan El Khalili Bazaar and admiring the stunning architecture of mosques such as the Alabaster Mosque of Muhammad Ali.\r\n\r\nDay 3: Alexandria: Greco-Roman Splendor\r\nTravel to Alexandria and explore its unique blend of history and modernity. Visit the Catacombs of Kom El Shoqafa, a remarkable burial site, and the impressive Qaitbay Citadel, offering panoramic views of the Mediterranean. Take a stroll along the picturesque Corniche and end your trip with a visit to the stunning Bibliotheca Alexandrina, a modern tribute to the ancient Library of Alexandria.\r\n\r\nHighlights:\r\n\r\n    Pyramids of Giza: Stand before the ancient wonders and ponder the mysteries of the pyramids.\r\n    Egyptian Museum: Delve into Egypt\'s history through its vast collection of artifacts and treasures.\r\n    Islamic Cairo: Experience the vibrant atmosphere of the bazaars and the elegance of Islamic architecture.\r\n    Alexandria\'s Charm: Discover the coastal city\'s Greco-Roman heritage and modern attractions.\r\n    Cultural Insights: Gain insights into Egypt\'s fascinating past and vibrant present.\r\n\r\nAccommodations:\r\nStay in well-appointed hotels in both Cairo and Alexandria, offering comfort and convenience for your exploration of these cities.\r\n\r\nThis 3-day journey through Cairo and Alexandria offers a glimpse into Egypt\'s storied past and dynamic present. Explore ancient wonders, vibrant markets, and modern marvels as you immerse yourself in the captivating history and culture of these two enchanting cities.', 3, '2024-02-09', 400, 'CairoMI.jpg,Alexandria.jpg', 0, 0.0),
(12, 'Jerusalem, Tel Aviv, Acre', 'Israel', '10 Days in Israel: Exploring Jerusalem, Tel Aviv, and Acre.', 'Embark on a captivating 10-day journey through Israel, a land of diverse cultures, historical treasures, and modern marvels. From the spiritual heart of Jerusalem to the vibrant streets of Tel Aviv and the ancient port city of Acre, this trip promises a rich and memorable experience.\r\n\r\nDay 1-4: Jerusalem - Spiritual and Historical Center\r\nBegin your adventure in Jerusalem, a city steeped in religious significance and historical importance. Explore the Old City\'s quarters – Jewish, Christian, Muslim, and Armenian – and visit iconic sites such as the Western Wall, Church of the Holy Sepulchre, and Dome of the Rock. Immerse yourself in the city\'s vibrant marketplaces and enjoy panoramic views from the Mount of Olives.\r\n\r\nDay 5-7: Tel Aviv - Modern Urban Delights\r\nTravel to Tel Aviv, Israel\'s cosmopolitan hub known for its lively culture and beautiful beaches. Spend your days exploring the city\'s contemporary art scene, strolling along the promenade, and enjoying its vibrant nightlife. Visit the historic district of Neve Tzedek, the bustling Carmel Market, and the trendy Rothschild Boulevard.\r\n\r\nDay 8-10: Acre (Akko) - Ancient Port City\r\nHead north to the ancient port city of Acre, known for its rich history and well-preserved architecture. Explore the UNESCO-listed Old City, including the Crusader Fortress, bustling market, and stunning sea views. Visit the Bahá\'í Gardens in nearby Haifa and experience the harmonious coexistence of cultures.\r\n\r\nHighlights:\r\n\r\n    Jerusalem\'s Old City: Experience the spiritual aura and historical layers of this ancient city.\r\n    Tel Aviv\'s Beaches: Relax on the sandy shores and explore the vibrant cultural scene.\r\n    Acre\'s Heritage: Wander through the winding streets of the well-preserved Old City.\r\n    Cultural Encounters: Engage with diverse communities and learn about their traditions.\r\n    Gastronomic Delights: Savor Israeli cuisine, from falafel to gourmet dining.\r\n\r\nAccommodations:\r\nStay in comfortable hotels in each city, offering convenient access to attractions and amenities.\r\n\r\nThis 10-day exploration of Jerusalem, Tel Aviv, and Acre allows you to experience the diverse facets of Israel – from its ancient roots to its modern vibrancy. Encounter spiritual sites, cultural landmarks, and the warmth of the local people as you journey through this captivating country.', 10, '2023-11-04', 2100, 'Acre.jpg,JerusalemMI.jpg,TelAviv.jpg', 0, 0.0),
(13, 'San Jose', 'Costa Rica', '7 Days in Costa Rica: Discovering San Jose and Surroundings.', 'Experience the natural beauty, cultural richness, and vibrant city life of Costa Rica in a 7-day adventure that combines the bustling capital city of San Jose with the captivating surroundings. From lush rainforests to picturesque beaches, this trip offers a taste of Costa Rica\'s diverse landscapes.\r\n\r\nDay 1-3: San Jose - Urban Exploration and History\r\nArrive in San Jose, the capital city, and immerse yourself in its lively atmosphere. Explore the historic neighborhoods, visit the National Museum, and wander through local markets. Experience the city\'s art and theater scene and indulge in traditional Costa Rican cuisine.\r\n\r\nDay 4-5: La Paz Waterfall Gardens - Natural Wonders\r\nEmbark on a journey to La Paz Waterfall Gardens, a nature reserve renowned for its waterfalls, wildlife, and tropical gardens. Hike through lush rainforests, witness stunning waterfalls, and encounter toucans, butterflies, and monkeys. Relax in the on-site hot springs for a rejuvenating experience.\r\n\r\nDay 6-7: Manuel Antonio National Park - Beach and Wildlife\r\nHead to Manuel Antonio National Park, a coastal gem known for its pristine beaches and rich biodiversity. Hike through the park\'s trails and spot monkeys, sloths, and exotic birds. Relax on the white sand beaches, take a dip in the turquoise waters, and bask in the beauty of the Pacific coastline.\r\n\r\nHighlights:\r\n\r\n    San Jose\'s Cultural Scene: Discover art, history, and local life in the capital city.\r\n    La Paz Waterfall Gardens: Experience Costa Rica\'s natural beauty with waterfalls and wildlife.\r\n    Manuel Antonio National Park: Encounter diverse flora and fauna in a coastal paradise.\r\n    Beach Bliss: Enjoy the sun and sea on Manuel Antonio\'s stunning beaches.\r\n\r\nAccommodations:\r\nStay in comfortable accommodations ranging from boutique hotels in San Jose to eco-friendly lodges near La Paz Waterfall Gardens and beachfront resorts in Manuel Antonio.\r\n\r\nThis 7-day exploration of San Jose and its surroundings offers a blend of urban experiences, natural wonders, and serene beaches. Immerse yourself in Costa Rica\'s rich culture, diverse landscapes, and abundant wildlife for an unforgettable adventure.', 7, '2023-09-30', 2300, 'SanJoseMI.jpg', 1, 0.0),
(14, 'Sydney, Cairns', 'Australia', '14 Days in Australia: Sydney, Cairns, and Extreme Adventures.', 'Embark on an exhilarating 14-day journey through the stunning landscapes of Australia, from the bustling city of Sydney to the tropical paradise of Cairns. This action-packed itinerary offers a mix of extreme sports, breathtaking natural wonders, and unforgettable experiences.\r\n\r\nDay 1-3: Sydney - City Exploration and Skydiving\r\nArrive in Sydney and dive right into the urban energy. Explore iconic landmarks like the Sydney Opera House and Sydney Harbour Bridge. Experience the thrill of a lifetime with a tandem skydiving adventure, where you\'ll leap from an airplane and enjoy breathtaking views of the city and coastline.\r\n\r\nDay 4-6: Blue Mountains - Hiking and Abseiling\r\nVenture to the Blue Mountains for exhilarating outdoor activities. Hike through lush forests, discover stunning waterfalls, and experience the thrill of abseiling down rock formations. Capture panoramic views of the dramatic landscapes that earned the region its name.\r\n\r\nDay 7-9: Canberra and Snowy Mountains - Adrenaline-Fueled Stops\r\nEn route to Sydney, make a stop in Canberra, Australia\'s capital, to explore its cultural attractions. Then, head to the Snowy Mountains for adrenaline-pumping adventures such as skiing or snowboarding during the winter months.\r\n\r\nDay 10-12: Cairns - Reef and Rainforest\r\nFly to Cairns, your gateway to the Great Barrier Reef and the Daintree Rainforest. Snorkel or dive in the vibrant coral reefs, witness an underwater wonderland, and discover marine life. Explore the Daintree Rainforest, one of the world\'s oldest rainforests, and engage in zip-lining and jungle trekking.\r\n\r\nDay 13-14: Cairns - Bungee Jumping and Relaxation\r\nConclude your adventure with a thrilling bungee jumping experience from the AJ Hackett Cairns Bungy Tower, surrounded by lush rainforest. Alternatively, unwind on the picturesque beaches of Cairns, soaking in the tropical vibes and reflecting on your incredible journey.\r\n\r\nHighlights:\r\n\r\n    Skydiving Over Sydney: Experience a rush of adrenaline while enjoying stunning city views.\r\n    Blue Mountains Adventure: Hike, abseil, and marvel at the Blue Mountains\' natural beauty.\r\n    Snowy Mountains: Ski or snowboard in the winter wonderland of the Snowy Mountains.\r\n    Great Barrier Reef: Explore the vibrant underwater world of the world-famous reef.\r\n    Daintree Rainforest: Zip-line and trek through the ancient Daintree Rainforest.\r\n    Bungee Jumping: Take a leap of faith from the AJ Hackett Bungy Tower.\r\n\r\nAccommodations:\r\nStay in a mix of city hotels, charming lodges in the Blue Mountains, and tropical resorts in Cairns.\r\n\r\nGet ready for an adrenaline-pumping journey as you explore the best of Sydney, experience heart-pounding adventures, and discover the natural wonders of Cairns. This itinerary promises an unforgettable and action-packed Australian adventure.', 14, '2024-07-10', 5500, 'SydneyMI.jpg,Cairns.jpg', 0, 0.0),
(15, 'Barcelona', 'Spain', '5 Days in Barcelona, Spain: Gaudi\'s Masterpieces and Mediterranean Vibes.', 'Embark on a captivating 5-day journey through Barcelona, Spain\'s vibrant and cultural hub. This itinerary allows you to explore the city\'s iconic architecture, savor its culinary delights, and soak in the Mediterranean ambiance.\r\n\r\nDay 1: Arrival and Gothic Quarter\r\nArrive in Barcelona and dive into the heart of the city by exploring the historic Gothic Quarter. Stroll through narrow streets lined with medieval buildings, visit Barcelona Cathedral, and discover hidden squares brimming with local charm. Enjoy tapas and paella at a traditional bodega.\r\n\r\nDay 2: Modernisme Marvels\r\nDiscover the architectural wonders of Antoni Gaudí. Begin with the awe-inspiring Sagrada Família, an unfinished masterpiece that combines Gothic and Art Nouveau styles. Explore Park Güell\'s colorful mosaics and whimsical structures, offering panoramic views of the city.\r\n\r\nDay 3: Montjuïc and Picasso\r\nAscend Montjuïc Hill for a sweeping view of Barcelona\'s skyline and its port. Visit the Montjuïc Castle and explore the MNAC Museum with its impressive Catalan art collection. In the afternoon, delve into the creative genius of Picasso at the Picasso Museum.\r\n\r\nDay 4: Beach and La Rambla\r\nSpend your morning relaxing on the sandy shores of Barceloneta Beach, basking in the Mediterranean sun. In the afternoon, take a leisurely stroll along La Rambla, Barcelona\'s famous boulevard, known for its lively atmosphere, street performers, and bustling markets.\r\n\r\nDay 5: Day Trip to Montserrat or Tibidabo\r\nChoose between a day trip to Montserrat, a unique mountain with a monastery perched on its cliffs, or a visit to Tibidabo Mountain, home to an amusement park and panoramic views of the city. Conclude your trip with a farewell dinner at a beachfront restaurant.\r\n\r\nHighlights:\r\n\r\n    Gothic Quarter: Explore the charming alleyways and historic sites of Barcelona\'s Gothic Quarter.\r\n    Sagrada Família: Marvel at the intricate architecture of Gaudí\'s iconic basilica.\r\n    Park Güell: Admire the vibrant mosaics and playful designs of Gaudí\'s park.\r\n    Montjuïc Hill: Enjoy panoramic views from Montjuïc and explore its cultural attractions.\r\n    Picasso Museum: Immerse yourself in the works of the legendary artist Pablo Picasso.\r\n    Barceloneta Beach: Relax and unwind on the city\'s sandy Mediterranean beach.\r\n    La Rambla: Experience the vibrant street life and markets along La Rambla.\r\n    Day Trip Choice: Explore the spiritual Montserrat or enjoy fun at Tibidabo.\r\n\r\nAccommodations:\r\nStay in charming boutique hotels, stylish urban retreats, or beachfront accommodations in Barcelona.\r\n\r\nExperience the essence of Barcelona\'s rich culture, stunning architecture, and Mediterranean allure as you uncover its historic districts, admire Gaudí\'s masterpieces, and savor its delectable cuisine. This itinerary promises a delightful and immersive exploration of this captivating city.', 5, '2023-10-30', 1300, 'BarcelonaMI.jpg', 2, 0.0),
(16, 'Tokyo', 'Japan', '7 Days in Tokyo, Japan: A Fusion of Tradition and Modernity.', 'Embark on an enchanting 7-day journey through Tokyo, Japan\'s vibrant capital. This itinerary takes you on a captivating exploration of the city\'s rich cultural heritage, futuristic innovations, and iconic landmarks.\r\n\r\nDay 1: Arrival and Shinjuku\'s Neon Lights\r\nArrive in Tokyo and immerse yourself in the dazzling lights of Shinjuku. Wander through bustling streets, admire the towering skyscrapers, and enjoy a taste of Japanese street food. Experience the energetic atmosphere of one of Tokyo\'s most iconic districts.\r\n\r\nDay 2: Tokyo\'s Past and Present\r\nVisit the serene Meiji Shrine, nestled within the lush Yoyogi Park. Explore Harajuku\'s trendy fashion scene and enjoy shopping in Takeshita Street. In the afternoon, delve into the historical district of Asakusa, where you\'ll find the iconic Senso-ji Temple and Nakamise Street\'s charming shops.\r\n\r\nDay 3: Tsukiji Outer Market and Odaiba Island\r\nBegin your day at Tsukiji Outer Market, savoring the freshest seafood and local delicacies. Head to Odaiba Island, a futuristic entertainment hub with attractions like the Rainbow Bridge and teamLab Borderless, an immersive digital art museum.\r\n\r\nDay 4: Day Trip to Nikko\'s Temples and Nature\r\nEscape to Nikko, a UNESCO World Heritage site known for its stunning temples and lush landscapes. Explore Toshogu Shrine\'s intricate carvings and venture to the serene Lake Chuzenji. Admire the striking Kegon Falls and the vibrant Futarasan Shrine.\r\n\r\nDay 5: Shibuya Crossing and Akihabara\r\nWitness the famous Shibuya Crossing in action, a mesmerizing display of organized chaos. Explore Shibuya\'s fashionable boutiques and cafes. In the afternoon, immerse yourself in the anime and electronics paradise of Akihabara.\r\n\r\nDay 6: Modern Tokyo and Imperial Palace\r\nDiscover the modern architecture of Tokyo\'s Marunouchi district, home to the Imperial Palace. Stroll through the East Gardens and take in the tranquil scenery. Experience the city\'s high-tech innovation with a visit to TeamLab Planets or TeamLab Borderless.\r\n\r\nDay 7: Farewell and Tokyo Skytree\r\nConclude your journey with a visit to Tokyo Skytree, one of the world\'s tallest towers. Take in panoramic views of the sprawling cityscape and reminisce about your week of unforgettable experiences. Spend your last hours shopping for souvenirs in trendy Shibuya.\r\n\r\nHighlights:\r\n\r\n    Shinjuku Lights: Dive into the neon-lit streets of Shinjuku for a taste of modern Tokyo.\r\n    Cultural Immersion: Explore historic sites like Meiji Shrine and Senso-ji Temple.\r\n    Futuristic Odaiba: Experience Tokyo\'s cutting-edge technology on Odaiba Island.\r\n    Nikko\'s Temples: Discover the spiritual beauty of Nikko\'s UNESCO-listed temples.\r\n    Anime and Electronics: Immerse yourself in Akihabara\'s subculture and gadget paradise.\r\n    Imperial Palace: Wander through the East Gardens and admire the Imperial Palace.\r\n    Sky-High Views: Take in the city from Tokyo Skytree\'s observation decks.\r\n\r\nAccommodations:\r\nStay in a mix of traditional ryokans, stylish boutique hotels, and modern accommodations in Tokyo.\r\n\r\nExperience the juxtaposition of Tokyo\'s timeless traditions and futuristic innovations as you journey through this captivating metropolis. This itinerary promises an enchanting and immersive exploration of Japan\'s dynamic capital.', 7, '2023-10-18', 2200, 'TokyoMI.jpg', 14, 0.0);
