(17, 'Istanbul', 'Turkey', '6 Days in Istanbul, Turkey: A Fusion of Cultures and History.', 'Embark on an enchanting 6-day journey through Istanbul, Turkey\'s vibrant and captivating metropolis that bridges the gap between Europe and Asia. This itinerary invites you to explore the city\'s rich history, diverse culture, and stunning architecture.\r\n\r\nDay 1: Arrival and Sultanahmet\r\nArrive in Istanbul and check into your hotel located in the historic Sultanahmet district. Begin your exploration by visiting the iconic Hagia Sophia, a marvel of Byzantine architecture that has witnessed centuries of history. Wander through the Blue Mosque\'s elegant courtyards and impressive domes.\r\n\r\nDay 2: Topkapi Palace and Grand Bazaar\r\nExplore the opulent Topkapi Palace, home to Ottoman sultans for centuries. Wander through its courtyards, pavilions, and treasury filled with priceless artifacts. Afterward, immerse yourself in the vibrant atmosphere of the Grand Bazaar, where you can shop for traditional Turkish carpets, ceramics, spices, and more.\r\n\r\nDay 3: Bosphorus Cruise and Spice Bazaar\r\nEmbark on a scenic Bosphorus cruise, sailing past historical landmarks and enjoying panoramic views of the city. Disembark at the Spice Bazaar, a sensory delight filled with colorful spices, teas, sweets, and Turkish delights. Enjoy a traditional Turkish tea at a waterfront cafe.\r\n\r\nDay 4: Chora Church and Suleymaniye Mosque\r\nVisit the Chora Church, renowned for its exquisite Byzantine mosaics and frescoes that depict biblical stories. Next, explore the Suleymaniye Mosque, an architectural masterpiece designed by the great Ottoman architect Mimar Sinan. Admire its grand dome and tranquil courtyards.\r\n\r\nDay 5: Beyoglu and Istiklal Avenue\r\nCross the Galata Bridge to the lively Beyoglu district. Walk along Istiklal Avenue, a bustling pedestrian street lined with shops, cafes, and historical landmarks. Ride the nostalgic red tram and visit the Galata Tower for panoramic views of the city.\r\n\r\nDay 6: Dolmabahce Palace and Farewell\r\nExplore the Dolmabahce Palace, a lavish Ottoman palace that showcases a blend of European and Ottoman architectural styles. Marvel at its grandeur, including the Crystal Staircase and the opulent Ceremonial Hall. Bid farewell to Istanbul with a traditional Turkish dinner accompanied by live music.\r\n\r\nHighlights:\r\n\r\n    Hagia Sophia: Discover the history and architectural marvel of the Hagia Sophia.\r\n    Blue Mosque: Admire the intricate blue tiles and stunning domes of the Blue Mosque.\r\n    Topkapi Palace: Explore the lavish palace that was once the heart of the Ottoman Empire.\r\n    Bosphorus Cruise: Enjoy a scenic cruise along the Bosphorus Strait.\r\n    Chora Church: Marvel at the intricate mosaics and frescoes of this Byzantine gem.\r\n    Suleymaniye Mosque: Visit the elegant mosque and its serene courtyards.\r\n    Istiklal Avenue: Experience the lively atmosphere of this bustling street.\r\n    Dolmabahce Palace: Explore the European-inspired palace on the Bosphorus shore.\r\n\r\nAccommodations:\r\nStay in charming boutique hotels or luxurious accommodations located in Istanbul\'s historic districts.\r\n\r\nExperience the magic of Istanbul as you journey through its splendid architecture, historic sites, and vibrant neighborhoods. This itinerary promises an immersive exploration of the city\'s rich heritage and cultural diversity.', 6, '2023-11-14', 1500, 'IstanbulMI.jpg', 0, 0.0),
(18, 'Alaska', 'Usa', '12-Day Alaska Exploration: A Journey Through Natural Wonders and Wildlife\n\n', '12-Day Alaska Exploration: A Journey Through Natural Wonders and Wildlife\r\n\r\nDay 1: Arrival in Anchorage\r\n\r\nArrive at Ted Stevens Anchorage International Airport.\r\nTransfer to your hotel in downtown Anchorage.\r\nExplore the city\'s vibrant downtown area and enjoy your first taste of Alaskan cuisine.\r\nDay 2: Anchorage to Girdwood\r\n\r\nDrive or take the Alaska Railroad to the charming town of Girdwood.\r\nVisit the Alaska Wildlife Conservation Center en route.\r\nCheck-in to your accommodation in Girdwood.\r\nDay 3: Girdwood and Alyeska Resort\r\n\r\nSpend the day at Alyeska Resort.\r\nChoose from activities like hiking, tram rides, or relaxation at the spa.\r\nEnjoy a fine dining experience with mountain views.\r\nDay 4: Kenai Fjords National Park\r\n\r\nTravel to Seward, gateway to Kenai Fjords National Park.\r\nEmbark on a full-day boat tour to witness glaciers, marine life, and stunning fjords.\r\nReturn to Seward for an overnight stay.\r\nDay 5: Denali Highway\r\n\r\nDrive along the scenic Denali Highway.\r\nExplore the remote beauty of the Alaska Range and stop for wildlife sightings.\r\nSpend the night in a rustic lodge or camp under the stars.\r\nDay 6: Denali National Park\r\n\r\nTravel to Denali National Park.\r\nTake a guided bus tour into the park for wildlife viewing and incredible landscapes.\r\nCheck-in to your accommodation near the park entrance.\r\nDay 7: Denali Adventure\r\n\r\nEnjoy a day of adventure activities such as hiking, rafting, or flightseeing.\r\nExplore the park\'s visitor center and nature trails.\r\nDay 8: Fairbanks\r\n\r\nDrive to Fairbanks, Alaska\'s Golden Heart City.\r\nVisit the Museum of the North and enjoy an optional riverboat tour.\r\nCheck-in to your Fairbanks accommodation.\r\nDay 9: Arctic Circle Adventure\r\n\r\nEmbark on an unforgettable journey to the Arctic Circle.\r\nCross the Arctic Circle, experience the midnight sun, and learn about indigenous cultures.\r\nReturn to Fairbanks for the night.\r\nDay 10: Fairbanks to Talkeetna\r\n\r\nDrive or take the train to Talkeetna.\r\nExplore the charming town and enjoy stunning views of Denali.\r\nCheck-in to your Talkeetna accommodation.\r\nDay 11: Talkeetna to Anchorage\r\n\r\nTravel back to Anchorage.\r\nSpend your last day shopping, visiting cultural centers, or hiking in Chugach State Park.\r\nCheck-in to your Anchorage accommodation.\r\nDay 12: Departure\r\n\r\nDepending on your flight time, you may have some free time in Anchorage before departing from Ted Stevens Anchorage International Airport.\r\nHighlights:\r\n\r\nScenic drives along the Denali Highway and breathtaking views of the Alaska Range.\r\nWildlife viewing in Denali National Park.\r\nExploration of Kenai Fjords National Park\'s glaciers and marine life.\r\nMidnight sun experiences in Fairbanks and the Arctic Circle.\r\nAdventure activities in Girdwood and Talkeetna.\r\nCultural and culinary experiences in Anchorage.\r\nAccommodations:\r\n\r\nStay in a variety of accommodations, from rustic lodges to comfortable hotels, all chosen for their unique Alaskan charm and accessibility to key attractions.\r\nPrice: Please contact our travel agency for a customized quote based on your preferences, group size, and travel dates. Prices vary depending on accommodations, activities, and other factors.\r\n\r\nDiscover the wild beauty, rich culture, and unforgettable experiences that Alaska has to offer on this 12-day adventure. Explore the Last Frontier and create lasting memories in one of the world\'s most captivating destinations.', 12, '2024-08-19', 7500, 'alaskaMI.jpg,alaskatwo.jpg,alaskathree.jpg', 11, 0.0),
(19, 'Amsterdam', 'Netherlands', '7-Day Amsterdam Adventure: Exploring Dutch Culture and Canals', '7-Day Amsterdam Adventure: Exploring Dutch Culture and Canals\r\n\r\nDay 1: Arrival in Amsterdam\r\n\r\nArrive at Amsterdam Airport Schiphol.\r\nCheck into your city center hotel.\r\nTake a leisurely walk along the picturesque canals.\r\nEnjoy a Dutch dinner at a local restaurant.\r\nDay 2: Explore the Historic Center\r\n\r\nVisit the iconic Anne Frank House (book tickets in advance).\r\nStroll through Dam Square and see the Royal Palace.\r\nExplore the historic Jordaan neighborhood with its charming streets.\r\nEvening canal cruise to see the city\'s landmarks lit up.\r\nDay 3: Museums and Art\r\n\r\nMorning at the Van Gogh Museum.\r\nAfternoon visit to the Rijksmuseum.\r\nExplore Museumplein and have lunch at a local café.\r\nEvening at leisure for shopping or a visit to Vondelpark.\r\nDay 4: Day Trip to Keukenhof Gardens (Seasonal)\r\n\r\nSpringtime visit to Keukenhof Gardens (March to May).\r\nEnjoy vibrant tulip fields and colorful flower displays.\r\nReturn to Amsterdam in the evening.\r\nDay 5: Day Trip to Zaanse Schans and Volendam\r\n\r\nExplore Zaanse Schans, a windmill village.\r\nVisit windmills, clog workshops, and cheese farms.\r\nContinue to Volendam, a charming fishing village.\r\nTry fresh seafood by the waterfront.\r\nDay 6: Canal Cruise and Hidden Gems\r\n\r\nMorning canal cruise to discover Amsterdam\'s waterways.\r\nExplore hidden gems like Begijnhof and De Pijp neighborhood.\r\nEvening at the vibrant Leidseplein area for dining and entertainment.\r\nDay 7: Farewell and Departure\r\n\r\nSpend your last morning exploring local markets or revisiting favorite spots.\r\nDepending on your flight time, depart from Amsterdam Airport Schiphol.\r\n\r\nDiscover the captivating charm of Amsterdam, from its historic treasures to its iconic canals. This 7-day journey promises an immersive experience that captures the essence of this enchanting Dutch city.', 7, '2024-01-02', 1500, 'amsterdamMI.jpg,amsterdamtwo.jpg,amsterdamthree.jpg', 2, 0.0),
(20, 'Cape Town', 'South Africa', '6-Day Cape Town Adventure: Exploring the Beauty of the Mother City', '6-Day Cape Town Adventure: Exploring the Beauty of the Mother City\r\n\r\nDay 1: Arrival in Cape Town\r\n\r\nArrive at Cape Town International Airport.\r\nCheck into your hotel in the city center.\r\nRelax and unwind after your journey.\r\nEnjoy dinner at a local restaurant.\r\nDay 2: Table Mountain and City Tour\r\n\r\nStart your day with a visit to Table Mountain (weather permitting).\r\nTake a cable car ride to the summit for panoramic views.\r\nExplore the city center with a guided walking tour.\r\nVisit historic landmarks like Greenmarket Square and Company\'s Garden.\r\nDiscover the vibrant atmosphere of Long Street.\r\nDay 3: Cape Peninsula Tour\r\n\r\nEmbark on a full-day Cape Peninsula tour.\r\nDrive along the stunning Chapman\'s Peak Drive.\r\nVisit Hout Bay, where you can take a boat to Seal Island (optional).\r\nExplore Cape Point and the Cape of Good Hope.\r\nStop at Boulders Beach to see the African penguin colony.\r\nReturn via Simon\'s Town and Kalk Bay for dinner.\r\nDay 4: Winelands Excursion\r\n\r\nHead to the Cape Winelands region.\r\nVisit Stellenbosch, a charming university town.\r\nEnjoy wine tastings at renowned vineyards.\r\nHave lunch in a winery with picturesque views.\r\nExplore the historic town of Franschhoek.\r\nReturn to Cape Town in the evening.\r\nDay 5: Robben Island and Waterfront\r\n\r\nMorning visit to Robben Island, a UNESCO World Heritage Site.\r\nTake a ferry to the former prison where Nelson Mandela was held.\r\nGuided tour by former political prisoners.\r\nAfternoon free time at the Victoria & Alfred Waterfront.\r\nEnjoy shopping, dining, or taking a sunset cruise.\r\nDay 6: Cape Point Nature Reserve\r\n\r\nExplore the Cape Point Nature Reserve at your own pace.\r\nTake a hike to the old lighthouse for stunning vistas.\r\nDiscover the indigenous flora and fauna of the reserve.\r\nVisit the historic naval town of Simon\'s Town.\r\nFarewell dinner at a seaside restaurant.\r\n\r\nExperience the diverse landscapes, rich history, and vibrant culture of Cape Town. This 6-day journey promises an immersive experience that captures the essence of the Mother City and its surroundings.', 6, '2022-10-24', 1300, 'capetownMI.jpg,capetowntwo.jpg,capetownfour.jpg', 0, 0.0),
(58, 'Los Angeles, New York', 'Usa', '6 days Coast to Coast Adventure: From New York to LA', 'Day 1: Explore the Big Apple\r\n\r\nStart your journey in the bustling metropolis of New York City.\r\nVisit iconic landmarks such as Times Square, Central Park, and the Statue of Liberty.\r\nEnjoy a Broadway show in the evening.\r\nDay 2: Journey to the Heartland\r\n\r\nDepart from New York and travel westward towards the heartland of America.\r\nStop in Chicago, known for its architecture and deep-dish pizza.\r\nExplore Millennium Park and the famous Cloud Gate sculpture.\r\nDay 3: The Great Plains\r\n\r\nContinue your adventure through the Great Plains of America.\r\nVisit Mount Rushmore and witness the iconic presidential sculptures.\r\nOvernight stay in Rapid City, South Dakota.\r\nDay 4: Rocky Mountain Majesty\r\n\r\nHead towards the stunning Rocky Mountains.\r\nExplore Yellowstone National Park, home to geysers and hot springs.\r\nMarvel at Old Faithful and the Grand Canyon of the Yellowstone.\r\nDay 5: Wild West Adventures\r\n\r\nContinue your journey westward into the Wild West.\r\nStop in Denver, Colorado, and discover its cultural and outdoor attractions.\r\nEnjoy a scenic hike or visit a local brewery.\r\nDay 6: Arrival in Los Angeles\r\n\r\nArrive in Los Angeles, the City of Angels.\r\nExplore Hollywood, walk along the Walk of Fame, and visit Griffith Observatory.\r\nConclude your cross-country adventure with a farewell dinner.\r\nThis 6-day cross-country tour will take you from the vibrant streets of New York City to the scenic beauty of the American West, finally culminating in the glitz and glamour of Los Angeles. Get ready for an unforgettable journey across the United States!', 6, '2023-11-11', 2449, 'vincentas-liskauskas-ErMkvcFla74-unsplashMI.jpg,tony-wiek-i1Yt31-Onuo-unsplashMI.jpg', 1, 0.0),
(59, 'Brazil, Bolivia, Argentina, Chile, Colombia', 'South america', '24 day South American Adventure: Exploring Brazil, Bolivia, Argentina, Chile & Colombia', 'Day 1: Arrival in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil\r\nArrive in Rio de Janeiro, check into your accommodation, and relax.\r\nDay 2-3: Explore Rio de Janeiro, Brazil\r\nVisit iconic landmarks like Christ the Redeemer, Sugarloaf Mountain, and Copacabana Beach.\r\nDay 4-5: Journey to the Amazon Rainforest, Brazil\r\nFly to Manaus, gateway to the Amazon Rainforest. Explore the lush jungle and take a river cruise.\r\nDay 6: Travel to La Paz, Bolivia\r\nFly to La Paz, Bolivia\'s capital, and explore the city\'s unique culture and architecture.\r\nDay 7-8: Explore La Paz and Salar de Uyuni, Bolivia\r\nVisit La Paz\'s markets and attractions, then explore the stunning Salar de Uyuni salt flats.\r\nDay 9-10: Discover Sucre and Potosi, Bolivia\r\nExplore the colonial charm of Sucre and the mining history of Potosi.\r\nDay 11-12: Explore Salta and Jujuy, Argentina\r\nDiscover the natural beauty and rich culture of Salta and Jujuy in Argentina.\r\nDay 13-14: Buenos Aires, Argentina\r\nExplore the vibrant capital city of Argentina, Buenos Aires.\r\nDay 15-16: Santiago, Chile\r\nVisit Santiago, the capital of Chile, and explore its attractions.\r\nDay 17-18: Atacama Desert, Chile\r\nExplore the otherworldly landscapes of the Atacama Desert.\r\nDay 19-20: San Pedro de Atacama and Uyuni, Bolivia\r\nTravel from Chile to Bolivia, visiting Uyuni and its salt flats.\r\nDay 21-22: Bogotá, Colombia\r\nExplore the capital city of Colombia, Bogotá, and its cultural treasures.\r\nDay 23-24: Medellín, Colombia\r\nConclude your journey in Medellín, known for its transformation and vibrant culture.\r\nThis simplified itinerary provides an overview of your 24-day trip through these South American countries, omitting headers and prices for each day.', 24, '2023-12-08', 6500, 'olga-stalska-QaWRyEdlffY-unsplashMI.jpg,alain-bonnardeaux-Zd6h7n442Og-unsplashMI.jpg,saul-mercado-LFuFLGo_3ME-unsplashMI.jpg,derek-oyen-lYv3hXpFdeY-unsplashMI.jpg,raphael-nogueira-OkiDIla7K8Q-unsplashMI.jpg', 4, 0.0),
